The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Wednesday, May 18, 2005 

 Leader son shot in sleep

 Calcutta, May 17: Bapi Purkait, 22, the son of a CPM panchayat member, was shot dead in sleep last night at Joynagar in South 24-Parganas, 75 km from Calcutta, a day after party leader Kalipada Naskar was brutally killed in the same district. 

 Bapis mother Kalidasi is a member of the Khakurda panchayat. Local CPM leaders blamed the SUCI for the murder. 

 Police have recovered a pistol left behind by the assailants, who climbed to Purkaits first-floor bedroom. No arrests were reported till late night. The SUCI blamed rivalry with the CPM for the death.




